  "diary": "Started the day right—Biscuit got his breakfast, sourdough starter was bubbly and happy, and I had my coffee on the patio before the day got loud. The transit strike meant I bit the bullet on rideshare surge pricing, which stung a bit, but I made it downtown in time. Pharmacy was steady: the usual parade of refills and people asking if ibuprofen would help their Thursday aches. Grabbed lunch at Pike Place around noon—just me, a warm bowl of soup, and the noise of the market fading into background. Afternoon flew by. The best part was catching the bus home at 2:50 when everything went back to normal; no more surge pricing, just regular commute vibes. Fed Biscuit, shaped the sourdough, made something simple for dinner. Had a video call with Sarah over tea—she's dealing with some work stuff, and it was good to just listen. Ended the evening the way I like: reading, music, Biscuit warm against my leg. Felt settled.",
